#*************************************************************************
#                          Reweight Density Module                       *
#                      Adding density matrix to LO event                 *
#                                                                        *
#*************************************************************************
#          
#   1) the value of alpha_s will be used from the event so the value in
#      the param_card is not taken into account.
#      event generation runs are needed.
#   2) all inputs except particle_in_density_matrix are optional and
#      the accepted values are described in [paper].
#
#   For more detail on the inputs and how to use the density module, see [paper].
#   helicity_direction: choose 1 or more particles to act as reference for the definition of the helicity referential (appendix ... of [paper])
#   particle_in_density_matrix: choose 2 particles to put in the density matrix to study their spin correlations
#   boost_choice: choose 1 or more particles to boost the frame into their center-of-mass frame

#   order_helicities: helicity basis for the density matrix, for instance [1, 1, 1, -1, -1, 1, -1, -1] corresponds to {|++>, |+->, |-+>, |-->}
#   axis_referential: choose 1 particle in the initial state from which the production angle theta should be defined 
#   symmetrise_initial_state: if True, for each event the density matrix is computed as the sum of rho(theta) and rho(theta + pi)
#************************************************************************
# ENTER YOUR COMMANDS BELOW. 
#************************************************************************


#Default values:
change helicity_direction [-1] 
change particle_in_density_matrix [6, -6] 
change boost_choice [-1]
change order_helicities None
change axis_referential None
change symmetrise_initial_state False
